  🔠 functions.OpenWebPage:3 | Return {'content': '## Summary\n\nFactorial Energy, a solid-state battery developer, is planning to go public via a SPAC merger in mid-2026 to fund commercialization. This follows a real-world test where its batteries powered a modified Mercedes EQS for over 745 miles (1,200 km) on a single charge. The company is targeting 2027 for initial battery deployment in electric vehicles.\n\n## Key Points\n\n1.  **Real-World Performance:** A Mercedes EQS equipped with Factorial\'s 106 Ah solid-state battery cells drove over 745 miles (1,200 km) on a single charge in a September 2025 test and still had charge remaining. (Source: [https://electrek.co/2025/09/09/mercedes-eqs-with-solid-state-ev-batteries-drove-750-miles/](https://electrek.co/2025/09/09/mercedes-eqs-with-solid-state-ev-batteries-drove-750-miles/))\n2.  **Commercialization Partners:** Factorial is working with major automakers Mercedes-Benz, Stellantis, and Hyundai Motor to commercialize its technology. (Source: Article body)\n3.  **Lab Validation:** Stellantis validated Factorial\'s 77 Ah cells in lab testing, confirming "high energy density, fast charging, and robust performance across temperature extremes." (Source: [https://electrek.co/2025/04/28/jeep-dodge-maker-validates-solid-state-ev-batteries-coming-soon/](https://electrek.co/2025/04/28/jeep-dodge-maker-validates-solid-state-ev-batteries-coming-soon/))\n4.  **Public Listing Plan:** The company will go public through a business merger with special-purpose acquisition company (SPAC) Cartesian Growth Corporation III. The deal, valued at ~$1.1 billion, is expected to close in mid-2026 and will provide $100 million in growth funding. The company will list on Nasdaq under the ticker "FAC". (Source: [https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20251218768916/en/Factorial-and-Cartesian-Growth-Corporation-III-Nasdaq-CGCT-Announce-Business-Combination-Agreement-to-Accelerate-Commercialization-of-Solid-State-Battery-Technology](https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20251218768916/en/Factorial-and-Cartesian-Growth-Corporation-III-Nasdaq-CGCT-Announce-Business-Combination-Agreement-to-Accelerate-Commercialization-of-Solid-State-Battery-Technology))\n5.  **Market Launch Target:** CEO Dr. Siyu Huang stated the batteries could be powering EVs as soon as 2027, likely launching first in high-performance or luxury models like the Dodge Charger Daytona. (Source: [The New York Times interview](https://www.nytimes.com/2025/12/18/business/energy-environment/factorial-electric-vehicle-battery-spac.html), [https://electrek.co/2024/10/23/dodge-charger-ev-getting-solid-state-batteries-2026/](https://electrek.co/2024/10/23/dodge-charger-ev-getting-solid-state-batteries-2026/))\n\n## Technical Details\n\n*   **Cell Specifications:** The company has developed at least two cell formats:\n    *   A **106 Ah cell** used in the Mercedes EQS road test.\n    *   A **77 Ah cell** validated by Stellantis in lab testing.\n*   **Claimed Advantages:** CEO Huang states the solid-state platform delivers "longer range, lighter weight, and greater cost efficiency" compared to existing batteries. (Source: Businesswire statement)\n*   **Additional Markets:** Beyond EVs, Factorial plans to offer cells for defense, aerospace, and robotics.\n\n## References & Citations\n\n- [https://electrek.co/2025/09/09/mercedes-eqs-with-solid-state-ev-batteries-drove-750-miles/](https://electrek.co/2025/09/09/mercedes-eqs-with-solid-state-ev-batteries-drove-750-miles/)\n- [https://electrek.co/2025/04/28/jeep-dodge-maker-validates-solid-state-ev-batteries-coming-soon/](https://electrek.co/2025/04/28/jeep-dodge-maker-validates-solid-state-ev-batteries-coming-soon/)\n- [https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20251218768916/en/Factorial-and-Cartesian-Growth-Corporation-III-Nasdaq-CGCT-Announce-Business-Combination-Agreement-to-Accelerate-Commercialization-of-Solid-State-Battery-Technology](https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20251218768916/en/Factorial-and-Cartesian-Growth-Corporation-III-Nasdaq-CGCT-Announce-Business-Combination-Agreement-to-Accelerate-Commercialization-of-Solid-State-Battery-Technology)\n- [https://www.nytimes.com/2025/12/18/business/energy-environment/factorial-electric-vehicle-battery-spac.html](https://www.nytimes.com/2025/12/18/business/energy-environment/factorial-electric-vehicle-battery-spac.html)\n- [https://electrek.co/2024/10/23/dodge-charger-ev-getting-solid-state-batteries-2026/](https://electrek.co/2024/10/23/dodge-charger-ev-getting-solid-state-batteries-2026/)', 'links_on_page': ['https://electrek.co/', 'https://9to5mac.com/', 'https://9to5google.com/', 'https://9to5toys.com/', 'https://dronedj.com', 'https://spaceexplored.com', 'https://electrek.co/about/', 'https://9to5mac.com/privacy/', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCcOIZzJgLCyMPILY7-1Vsdg', 'https://www.twitter.com/electrekco', 'https://www.facebook.com/electrekco', 'https://www.instagram.com/electrek.co/', 'https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/electrek/id1320055779', 'https://electrek.co/follow-electrek/', 'https://apple.news/TDaZAAzogTHK5rrJYn3D6eQ', 'https://b.smartnews.be/r/3p2BcxbJznlh4Xi4', 'https://bsky.app/profile/electrek.co', 'https://flipboard.com/@electrek', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/electrek', 'https://electrek.co/push/', 'https://electrek.beehiiv.com/subscribe', 'https://electrek.co/contact-electrek/', 'https://electrek.co/forums/', 'https://electrek.co/best-electric-vehicle-prices/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/tesla/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/ford/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/gm/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/bmw/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/jaguar/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/vw/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/daimler/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/hyundai/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/nissan/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/Toyota/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/ebikes/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/electric-motorcycle/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/bus/', 'https://electrek.co/guides/hyper