  🔠 functions.OpenWebPage:7 | Return {'content': '## Summary\n\nThis article ranks the top 10 manufacturers developing solid-state batteries for electric vehicles, highlighting their key technologies, partnerships, and production timelines. The sector is focused on industrializing sulfide, oxide, and polymer electrolytes to improve energy density, charging speed, and safety, with mass production targets largely set for 2027-2030. (Source: https://evmagazine.com/top10/top-10-solid-state-ev-battery-manufacturers)\n\n## Key Points\n\n1.  **Industry Phase & Goals:** Solid-state battery development is shifting from pilot cells to scalable automotive platforms. The focus is on raising energy density, speeding up charging, improving safety, and lowering costs through dry-electrode lines and cell-to-pack integration. Mass production launches are targeted for 2027–2030. (Source: Introductory section)\n2.  **Solid Power (#10):** Specializes in sulfide-based solid electrolytes, targeting >500 miles of range and costs of ~$85/kWh. It has completed pilot lines and partners with BMW, Ford, Samsung SDI, and SK Innovation. (Source: Section 10)\n3.  **Enovix (#9):** Uses a 3D stacked architecture with a 100% silicon anode and a stainless-steel constraint system to minimize swelling to under 2% after 500 cycles. Its BrakeFlow technology adds abuse tolerance. (Source: Section 9)\n4.  **Gotion High-Tech (#8):** Unveiled the "Gemstone" all-solid-state battery with an energy density of 350 Wh/kg, passing a 200°C hot-box test. Its high-nickel NCM Stellary cylindrical battery can add 350km of range in 5 minutes. (Source: Section 8)\n5.  **NIO (#7):** Offers a 150 kWh semi-solid-state battery (developed with WeLion) delivering up to 577 miles of range, compatible with existing models. It collaborates with CATL on long-life batteries targeting 80% capacity retention after 12 years. (Source: Section 7)\n6.  **Samsung SDI (#6):** Completed its "S-Line" pilot production line in 2023, with mass production of solid-state batteries planned for 2027. Its roadmap targets 900 Wh/L solid-state batteries and cobalt-free designs. (Source: Section 6)\n7.  **CATL (#5):** Has developed a hybrid "condensed state" battery with prototype cells reaching 500 Wh/kg. Prototype production is in progress, targeting small-scale manufacturing for 2027. (Source: Section 5)\n8.  **LG Energy Solution (#4):** Invested $819M in R&D in 2023, establishing a Future Technology Center to work on solid-state and lithium-metal batteries. It targets solid-state mass production for 2030. (Source: Section 4)\n9.  **Nissan (#3):** Is building a prototype production facility for laminated all-solid-state battery (ASSB) cells, with a pilot line targeted for 2024. It aims for ASSB costs of $75/kWh by 2028 ($65 thereafter), promising twice the energy density of current lithium-ion. (Source: Section 3)\n10. **BYD (#2):** Its current Blade Battery (LFP) uses a Cell to Pack design, passing rigorous safety tests (nail penetration, crushing, 300°C heat). It is advancing solid-state research targeting up to 500 Wh/kg, with pilot output planned from 2027. (Source: Section 2)\n11. **Toyota (#1):** Pioneering solid-state batteries targeting 10-minute charging and a 20-50% range increase, with mass production aimed for 2027-28. Its 2026+ BEV roadmap includes three battery types offering 800km to >1,000km range. (Source: Section 1)\n\n## Technical Details\n\n*   **Electrolyte Types:** Manufacturers are industrializing **sulfide, oxide, and polymer** solid electrolytes. (Source: Introductory section)\n*   **Anode Materials:** Development focuses on **silicon-rich or lithium-metal anodes**. (Source: Introductory section)\n*   **Key Metrics:** Targets include energy densities from **350 Wh/kg (Gotion)** to **500 Wh/kg (CATL, BYD target)**, and cost targets down to **~$65/kWh (Nissan)**. (Source: Sections 8, 5, 2, 3)\n*   **Safety Testing:** Specific tests mentioned include the **Nail Penetration Test (BYD)** and a **200°C hot-box test (Gotion)**. (Source: Sections 2, 8)\n*   **Supporting Tech:** Advancements are linked to **dry-electrode manufacturing, Cell to Pack (CTP) integration**, and **pre-lithiation** processes. (Source: Introductory section, Sections 4, 9)\n\n## References & Citations\n\n- Source: https://evmagazine.com/top10/top-10-solid-state-ev-battery-manufacturers\n- Company-specific details sourced from respective numbered sections (1-10) within the main article body.', 'links_on_page': ['https://evmagazine.com/', 'https://evmagazine.com/', 'https://evmagazine.com/advertise', 'https://evmagazine.com/editorial', 'https://evmagazine.com/news', 'https://evmagazine.com/articles', 'https://evmagazine.com/interviews', 'https://evmagazine.com/top10', 'https://evmagazine.com/videos', 'https://evmagazine.com/events', 'https://evmagazine.com/magazines', 'https://sustainabilitymag.com/', 'https://energydigital.com/', 'https://evmagazine.com/company-reports', 'https://evmagazine.com/electric-cars', 'https://evmagazine.com/fleet-and-commercial', 'https://evmagazine.com/mobility', 'https://evmagazine.com/charging-and-infrastructure', 'https://evmagazine.com/sustainability', 'https://evmagazine.com/technology', 'https://evmagazine.com/self-drive', 'https://evmagazine.com/commute', 'https://sustainability-live.com/', 'https://evmagazine.com/advertise', 'https://evmagazine.com/editorial', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/evmagazine', 'https://twitter.com/EVMag_', 'https://www.facebook.com/EV-Magazine-101976739259665', 'https://www.instagram.com/ev_magazine', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCCwiFhiCQeuw-O_Zp6irFig?sub_confirmation=1', 'https://evmagazine.com/author/chloe-williment', 'https://evmagazine.com/articles/how-gotion-high-tech-is-revolutionising-battery-technologies', 'https://evmagazine.com/technology/nio-launches-smart-driving-technology-center-in-germany', 'https://evmagazine.com/news/tesla-secures-us-16-5bn-samsung-chip-manufacturing-deal', 'https://evmagazine.com/news/catl-dhl-expand-partnership-sustainable-logistics', 'https://evmagazine.com/articles/lg-energy-solution-mixed-q2-revenue-up-profits-down', 'https://evmagazine.com/news/will-nissans-roof-mounted-solar-panels-for-evs-catch-on', 'https://evmagazine.com/news/how-chinas-byd-is-using-ai-to-scale-global-ev-manufacturing', 'https://evmagazine.com/charging-and-infrastructure/toyota-and-evgo-expand-fast-charging-network-nationwide', 'https://evmagazine.com/company/byd', 'https://evmagazine.com/company/catl', 'https://evmagazine.com/company/enovix', 'https://evmagazine.com/company/gotion%20high%20tech', 'https://evmagazine.com/company/lg-energy-solution', 'https://evmagazine.com/company/nio', 'https://evmagazine.com/company/nissan', 'https://evmagazine.com/company/samsung-sdi', 'https://evmagazine.com/company/solid-power', 'https://evmagazine.com/company/toyota', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/david-dong-myung-kim', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/dong-li-67890', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/ivan-espinosa', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/john-van-scoter', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/joo-sun-choi', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/koji-sato', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/raj-talluri', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/wang-chuanfu', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/william-li', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/zeng-yuqun-robin-zeng', 'https://evmagazine.com/executive/zhen-li', 'https://evmagazine.com/search?q=EV', 'https://evmagazine.com/search?q=Battery', 'https://evmagazine.com/search?q=Manufacturing', 'https://evmagazine.com/search?q=Solid%20State', 'https://evmagazine.com/search?q=Sustainability', 'https://evmagazine.com/search?q=Mobility', 'https://evmagazine.com/magazine/ev-magazine-march-2026', 'https://evmagazine.com/company-reports', 'https://evmagazine.com/interviews', 'https://evmagazine.com/videos', 'https://evmagazine.com/events', 'https://evmagazine.com/top10', 'https://evmagazine.com/about', 'https://evmagazine.com/editorial',