  🔠 functions.OpenWebPage:6 | Return {'content': '## Summary\n\nThis article provides a comprehensive list of current and upcoming electric vehicles (EVs) that use or plan to use solid-state or semi-solid-state battery technology. It details specific models, their battery specifications, suppliers, and projected timelines for commercialization, highlighting that while semi-solid-state batteries are already in limited use in China, widespread adoption of all-solid-state batteries is expected later this decade.\n\n## Key Points\n\n1.  Solid-state batteries are considered a "holy grail" technology, promising an ideal balance of range, safety, performance, and fast-charging by replacing the liquid electrolyte with a solid one, though manufacturing at scale remains a challenge. (Source: Introduction section)\n2.  BloombergNEF projects solid-state batteries will account for only 10% of global EV and battery storage demand by 2035, with 83% of current or planned manufacturing capacity concentrated in China. (Source: Introduction section, BNEF citation)\n3.  **Current & Upcoming Models with Semi/All-Solid-State Batteries:**\n    *   **Karma Kaveya (Upcoming):** Plans to be the first U.S. carmaker with semi-solid-state batteries from Factorial Energy. (Source: Karma Kaveya section)\n    *   **Verge TS Pro/TS Ultra (2026):** Claims to be the first production motorcycle with all-solid-state batteries from Donut Labs (400 Wh/kg, 370+ mile range), though its claims have faced industry skepticism. (Source: Verge TS Pro/TS Ultra section)\n    *   **Nio ET7/ET5 (Available):** Offers a 150 kWh semi-solid-state battery (360 Wh/kg) from WeLion for rental in China, with a claimed 652-mile range demonstrated in a real-world test. (Source: Nio ET7/ET5 section)\n    *   **IM Motors L6 (Available):** Available with a 133 kWh semi-solid-state pack from QingTao, claiming 620+ miles of range (CLTC) and 900V architecture for ultra-fast charging. (Source: IM Motors L6 section)\n    *   **MG4 (Available):** Marketed as the first affordable mass-market EV with a 53.9 kWh semi-solid-state battery (180 Wh/kg) from QingTao, using only 5% liquid electrolyte. (Source: MG4 section)\n    *   **Demo Vehicles:** Several automakers are testing prototype batteries in demo fleets, including Dodge Charger Daytona (Factorial, 375 Wh/kg), Mercedes-Benz EQS (Factorial, +25% range claim), and BMW i7 (Solid Power, 390 Wh/kg). (Source: Dodge, Mercedes, BMW sections)\n\n## Technical Details\n\n*   **Battery Types:** The article distinguishes between **semi-solid-state** (gel-like electrolyte) and **all-solid-state** batteries.\n*   **Reported Energy Densities:**\n    *   Verge/Donut Labs: 400 Wh/kg (all-solid-state)\n    *   Nio/WeLion: 360 Wh/kg (semi-solid-state)\n    *   Dodge/Factorial: 375 Wh/kg (semi-solid-state)\n    *   BMW/Solid Power: 390 Wh/kg (all-solid-state)\n    *   MG4/QingTao: 180 Wh/kg (semi-solid-state)\n*   **Claimed Range & Charging Highlights:**\n    *   Nio ET7: 652 miles on a single charge (150 kWh pack).\n    *   IM L6: 620+ miles (CLTC); 248 miles of range in 12 minutes (900V architecture).\n    *   Rimac/ProLogium Prototype: 10-80% charge in 6.5 minutes (100 kWh pack).\n    *   Dodge/Factorial Prototype: 15-90% charge in 18 minutes at room temperature.\n\n## References & Citations\n\n- Source Article: https://insideevs.com/news/771402/every-solid-state-battery-ev/\n- BloombergNEF Report on manufacturing capacity: (Source: Introduction section, BNEF citation)\n- Nio\'s 648-mile range test: https://insideevs.com/news/701526/nio-et7-with-150-kwh-battery-covers-648-miles-single-charge/\n- Donut Labs industry skepticism: https://insideevs.com/news/785308/donut-labs-solid-state-skeptics-ces/\n- Rimac solid-state battery specs: https://insideevs.com/news/771520/rimac-solid-state-battery-specs/\n- Toyota solid-state battery patents: https://insideevs.com/news/598046/toyota-global-leader-solid-state-batery-patents/\n- Honda solid-state battery goals: https://insideevs.com/news/743468/honda-solid-state-ev-620-miles/\n- Volkswagen-QuantumScape funding: https://insideevs.com/news/767046/powerco-volkswagen-quantumscape-solid-state-battery/', 'links_on_page': ['https://insideevs.com/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/news/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/trending/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/charging/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/sales/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/critical-materials/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/technology/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/', 'https://insideevs.com/reviews/', 'https://insideevs.com/reviews/category/car-reviews/', 'https://insideevs.com/reviews/category/first-drives/', 'https://insideevs.com/reviews/category/tech-review/', 'https://insideevs.com/reviews/category/everything-we-know/', 'https://insideevs.com/reviews/category/test-drives/', 'https://insideevs.com/reviews/category/comparison/', 'https://insideevs.com/reviews/', 'https://insideevs.com/features/', 'https://insideevs.com/features/category/features/', 'https://insideevs.com/features/category/podcast/', 'https://insideevs.com/features/category/opinion/', 'https://insideevs.com/features/category/buying-advice/', 'https://insideevs.com/features/category/lists/', 'https://insideevs.com/features/category/breakthrough-awards/', 'https://insideevs.com/features/', 'https://insideevs.com/videos/', 'https://insideevs.com/features/category/podcast/', 'https://insideevs.com/photos/', 'https://update.insideevs.com/', 'https://insideevs.com/topic/513/best-evs/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/news/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/trending/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/charging/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/sales/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/critical-materials/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/category/technology/', 'https://insideevs.com/news/', 'https://insideevs.com/reviews/', 'https://insideev