     ## Executive Summary
     
     Solid-state batteries (SSBs) have moved from laboratory curiosity to pre-commercial reality in 2024-2025. While **mass-market EVs with true all-solid-state batteries are not yet available**, significant milestones have been achieved including real-world vehicle testing, validation by major automakers, and announced production timelines. The industry has shifted from "if" to "when"—with most major players targeting 2027-2030 for commercialization.
     
     ---
     
     ## 1. When Are They Actually Hitting the Market (Cars)?
     
     ### Current Status: Pre-Commercial Phase
     
     **Already on the Road (Limited/Semi-Solid State):**
     - **NIO ET7/ET5 (China):** Available with 150 kWh semi-solid-state batteries (360 Wh/kg) from WeLion, delivering up to 652 miles (1,048 km) range
     - **IM Motors L6 (China):** 133 kWh semi-solid-state pack from QingTao, claiming 620+ miles range
     - **MG4 (China):** Marketed as first affordable mass-market EV with 53.9 kWh semi-solid-state battery (180 Wh/kg)
     
     **Prototype/Demo Vehicles Testing:**
     - **Mercedes-Benz EQS:** Successfully tested with Factorial's 106 Ah lithium-metal solid-state battery, achieving **745+ miles (1,200 km)** on a single charge (September 2025 test)
     - **Dodge Charger Daytona:** Prototype testing with Factorial batteries (375 Wh/kg)
     - **BMW i7:** Testing sulfide-based solid electrolytes with Solid Power (390 Wh/kg)
     
     ### Commercial Launch Timelines
     
     | Company | Target Date | Vehicle Type | Notes |
     |---------|-------------|--------------|-------|
     | **Factorial Energy** | 2027 | Luxury/Performance EVs | Going public via SPAC in mid-2026 |
     | **Toyota** | 2027-2028 | Mass-market EVs | First iteration: 20% range increase, 10-min charging |
     | **Samsung SDI** | 2027 | Mass production | "S-Line" pilot line completed 2023 |
     | **Nissan** | 2028 | Mass-market EVs | Prototype facility operational |
     | **CATL** | 2027 | Small-scale production | Condensed state battery (500 Wh/kg) |
     | **BYD** | 2027 | Pilot production | Targeting 500 Wh/kg |
     | **LG Energy Solution** | 2030 | Mass production | $819M R&D investment |
     | **Solid Power** | Post-2027 | Various | Partners with BMW, Ford |
     | **Honda** | Late 2020s | EVs | Prototype production began 2025 |
     
     **Market Projection:** BloombergNEF estimates solid-state batteries will account for only **10% of global EV demand by 2035**, with 83% of manufacturing capacity concentrated in China.
     
